x4freetext: facility spallation neutron source at LANSCE (Los
Thin active target consisting of eight photovoltaic
cells, sensitive to fission fragments. On each solar
cell a 1 mg/cm2 layer of 238U was deposited. A very
thin solar cels were used to reduce x-ray attenuation.
HPGe array GEANIE, consisting of 26 high
resolution HPGe detectors. 11 detectors were of LEPS
type, dedicated to low energy photon spectroscopy in
For the x-ray measurements, x-rays were
detected in coincidence with fission fragments using
The energies of the incident neutrons are
determined by the time-of- flight between the
Neutrons were produced by spallation reaction
of 800 MeV protons impinging on W target. GEANIE
array was located 20 m from WNR spallation target at
the end of collimated flight path
Three different sets of data were used to identify
fission-gamma coincidences. Thanks to a complementary
analysis of the different types of measurement, about
one hundred fission fragments were identified.
